PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1777111603
OL,3,CPrince Harry: I will always be part of
OL,4,Cthe Royal Family
OL,6,FAnd he spoke of the need for "American
OL,7,Fleadership" on Ukraine after the USA
OL,8,Fhad previously pledged to protect the
OL,9,Fcountry when it gave up its nuclear
OL,10,Fweapons in the 1990s.
OL,12,FHarry didn't mention Donald Trump by
OL,13,Fname, but he did provoke a reaction
OL,14,Ffrom the US President last night, who
OL,15,Fsaid the prince "does not speak for
OL,16,Fthe UK".
OL,26,@nD@^OUoD@KO]xD@GO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1777111603
OL,3,CPrince Harry: I will always be part of
OL,4,Cthe Royal Family
OL,6,FGiven the risk that his words could
OL,7,Fmake things more difficult for King
OL,8,FCharles in the USA next week, we asked
OL,9,FHarry if he thought his speech in
OL,10,FUkraine would have an impact on the
OL,11,FState Visit.
OL,13,F"No, I don't think so. Not at all", he
OL,14,Freplied.
OL,16,FAs just about the whole world knows,
OL,17,FHarry and Meghan left the Royal Family
OL,18,Fin 2020, but the Duke of Sussex said
OL,19,Ftoday that he will always be part of
OL,20,Fit.
OL,26,@uD@AOUuD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
